 an entitled relative\">entitled relative</a>.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p><a href=\"/unclaimed-estates-bona-vacantia/make-a-claim-on-an-estate\" title=\"Make a claim on an estate\">Make a claim</a> on the estate.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If an estate is not listed, you can <a href=\"/unclaimed-estates-bona-vacantia/refer-an-estate\" title=\"Refer an estate\">tell the Crown about an estate</a> you think is unclaimed.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>If you&rsquo;re not a relative</h2>\n\n<p>If you think you may be entitled to a share of a deceased person&rsquo;s estate (eg if you lived together or you cared for them), you can <a href=\"/unclaimed-estates-bona-vacantia/grants-from-a-deceased-persons-estate\" title=\"Grants from a deceased person's estate\">apply for a grant from the estate</a>.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/unclaimed-estates-bona-vacantia/who-to-contact","slug":"who-to-contact","order":2,"title":"Who to contact","body":"<p>The <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.bonavacantia.gov.uk/output/estates.aspx\" title=\"Treasury Solicitor's Estates Group\">Treasury Solicitor&rsquo;s Estates Group</a> handles bona vacantia in England and Wales (except in the Duchies of Cornwall and Lancaster). </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>There’s a <a href=\"http://www.bonavacantia.gov.uk/output/estates-list.aspx\" title=\"list of unclaimed estates\" rel=\"external\">list of unclaimed estates</a> and some frequently-asked questions on the Treasury Solicitor’s website.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Adverts and claims</h2>\n\n<p>The Treasury Solicitor advertises to find entitled family. If you reply to an advert, you have to prove your relationship with the deceased, eg with a birth, marriage or death certificate.</p>\n\n<h2>Other bodies that represent the Crown</h2>\n\n<p>Elsewhere, bona vacantia is dealt with by:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>in the Duchies of Cornwall and Lancaster - <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.farrer.co.uk/\" title=\"Farrer and Co\">Farrer and Co</a></li>\n  <li>in Scotland - <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://qltr.gov.uk/content/bona-vacantia\" title=\"The Queen's and Lord Treasurer's Remembrancer\">The Queen&rsquo;s and Lord Treasurer&rsquo;s Remembrancer</a></li>\n  <li>in Northern Ireland - phone the Crown Solicitor&rsquo;s Office for Northern Ireland</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Crown Solicitor’s Office for Northern Ireland</strong>  </p>\n\n<p>028 9054 6037</p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/unclaimed-estates-bona-vacantia/check-if-youre-an-entitled-relative","slug":"check-if-youre-an-entitled-relative","order":3,"title":"Check if you're an entitled relative","body":"<p>Before making a claim on an estate you need to know if you&rsquo;re entitled. There are some general rules:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>if there&rsquo;s no will, the person&rsquo;s spouse or civil partner and then any children have first claim to the estate</li>\n  <li>if there&rsquo;s no spouse or child, anyone descended from a grandparent of the person is entitled to a share in the estate</li>\n  <li>if you&rsquo;re related by marriage you have no entitlement</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p><a href=\"/inherits-someone-dies-without-will\" title=\"Tool to help you discover if you're entitled to a share of someone's estate\">Find out if you’re entitled to a share of the estate</a>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Adopted people</h2>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re adopted:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you have the same rights as if you&rsquo;d been born into your adoptive family</li>\n  <li>you have no rights to an estate of your original birth family</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If the deceased person was adopted, only the adoptive family have rights to the estate.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/unclaimed-estates-bona-vacantia/make-a-claim-on-an-estate","slug":"make-a-claim-on-an-estate","order":4,"title":"Make a claim on an estate","body":"<p>If you think you&rsquo;re enti