ed.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h2>Post-mortems</h2>\n<p>To find out how the person died, the coroner may decide a post-mortem is needed. This can be done either in a hospital or mortuary.</p>\n\n<p>You can&rsquo;t object to a post-mortem - but the coroner must tell you (and the person&rsquo;s GP) when and where the examination will take place.</p>\n\n<p>After the post-mortem:</p>\n\n<ol class=\"steps\">\n<li><p>The coroner will release the body for a funeral once they have completed the post-mortem examinations and no further examinations are needed.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>If the body is released with no inquest, the coroner will send send a form (‘Pink Form - form 100B’) to the registrar stating the cause of death.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>If the body is to be cremated, the coroner will also send a ‘Certificate of Coroner - form Cremation 6’.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h2>If the coroner decides to hold an inquest</h2>\n<p>A coroner must hold an inquest if the cause of death is still unknown, or if the person: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>possibly died a violent or unnatural death</li>\n  <li>died in prison or police custody</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You can&rsquo;t register the death until after the inquest. The coroner is responsible for sending the relevant paperwork to the registrar.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/after-a-death/arrange-the-funeral","slug":"arrange-the-funeral","order":4,"title":"Arrange the funeral","body":"<p>The funeral can usually only take place after the death has been registered.</p>\n\n<h2>Funeral directors</h2>\n<p>Most people use a funeral director.</p>\n\n<p>Get more than one quote to compare costs. You should choose a funeral director who&rsquo;s a member of either:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.nafd.org.uk/funeral-advice/funeral-advice-home.aspx\" title=\"National Association of Funeral Directors (NAFD)\">National Association of Funeral Directors</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.saif.org.uk/website/index.html\" title=\"Society of Allied and Independent Funeral Directors\">Society of Allied and Independent Funeral Directors</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Both organisations have codes of practice and have to give you a price list when asked.</p>\n\n<p>Some local councils run their own <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://local.direct.gov.uk/LDGRedirect/index.jsp?LGSL=671&amp;LGIL=8&amp;ServiceName=Find%20out%20about%20a%20council%20funeral\" title=\"find out about a council funeral\">funeral services</a> - eg non-religious burials.</p>\n\n<h2>Arranging the funeral yourself</h2>\n\n<p>To arrange a funeral yourself, contact the Cemeteries and Crematorium Department of your local council.</p>\n\n<h2>Funeral costs</h2>\n<p>Funeral costs can include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>funeral director fees</li>\n  <li>things the funeral director pays for on your behalf (called &lsquo;disbursements&rsquo;) - eg a newspaper announcement about the death</li>\n  <li>local authority burial fees</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Often funeral directors list all these costs in their quote.</p>\n\n<h3>Paying for a funeral</h3>\n<p>The funeral can be paid:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>by you or other family members or friends</li>\n  <li>from a financial scheme the person had - eg a pre-paid funeral plan or insurance policy</li>\n  <li>from money from the person&rsquo;s estate (eg savings) - getting access to this is called applying for a &lsquo;grant of representation&rsquo;(sometimes called <a href=\"/wills-probate-inheritance\" title=\"applying for probate: getting a grant of representation\">&lsquo;applying for probate&rsquo;</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If you have difficulty paying for the funeral, apply for a <a href=\"/funeral-payments\" title=\"Funeral Payments: what you can get, eligibility and how to claim\">Funeral Payment</a>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Moving a body out of England or Wales</h2>\n<p>You need to get permission from a coroner to move a body for a funeral abroad. Apply at least 4 days before you want the body to be moved.</p>\n\n<p>Find a local coroner using the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.coronersociety.org.uk/wfOfficeCoroner.aspx\" title=\"find a local coroner on the Coroners' Society of England and Wales website\">Coroners&rsquo; Society of England and Wales website.</a></p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/after-a-death/organisations-you-need-to-contact-and-tell-us-once","slug":"organisations-you-need-to-contact-and-tell-us-once","order":5,"title":"Organisations you need to contact and Tell Us Once","body":"<p>Most local councils run a service called Tell Us Once - they’ll contact different government services for you.</p>\n\n<p>Once you&rsquo;ve <a href=\"register-the-death\" title=\"register the death\">registered the death</a>, the registrar will explain your options for using Tell Us Once. These are:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>in person, by making an appointment with your local authority bereavement adviser</li>\n  <li>by phone – the registrar will give you the phone number</li>\n  <li>online</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Your registrar will give you a unique reference number to use <a href=\"https://death-tellusonce.direct.gov.uk/Death/Enrich/Recover\" title=\"Tell Us Once\" rel=\"external\">Tell Us Once online</a>, which you’ll need to log in.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>If you don&rsquo;t use Tell Us Once, you may need to contact the following organisations.</p>\n\n<h2>HM Revenue &amp; Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>)</h2>\n<p>You may need to contact <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://search2.hmrc.gov.uk/kb5/hmrc/contactus/view.page?record=7JTJEvPnPuo\" title=\"contact HMRC\"><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr></a> to fill in a <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/sa/behalf-who-has-died.htm\" title=\"completing a tax return on behalf of someone who has died\">tax return</a> for the deceased or <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/inco